# FindFoundFast

- **Split deploy:** Lovable **designs** the marketing site → `findfoundfast.com`. **You run the product** in **this repo** (Next + Supabase) → `app.findfoundfast.com` — auth, data, APIs, dashboards, link flows, and all engineering. Lovable does not “run” the business; it supplies the marketing UI. CTAs: `https://app.findfoundfast.com/get-started`. See **`ARCHITECTURE.md`**.
- **Site:** timed **photo + gate-code links** for deliveries/guests (no driver app).
- **Flows:** (1) **Property manager** — one-time building setup, 4 photos, one permanent link per building. (2) **Resident** — 5-char code, pick timer, copy timed link. (3) **Driver/guest** — tap link, see steps + codes; timer ends → link dies.
- **Marketing:** Lovable = public **design** for apex domain. **This repo** still owns app routes: `/pricing`, `/how-it-works`, `/get-started`, `/auth/login`, `/manager`, `/resident`, `/link/[slug]`, etc.
- **Stack:** Next.js App Router, Tailwind (`tailwind.config.js` + `lib/design-tokens.js`), Supabase, Vercel. Fonts: DM Sans + Space Mono (`app/layout.js`); align with Lovable fonts when needed.
- **Voice:** bold, fun, anti-frustration; taglines include “Google Maps for your food and your homies” / “FFFliping Cool”.

**Product brief:** `AGENTS.md`. **Repo split + routes:** `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
